<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How does bin-level addressed storage differ from bulk storage?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>In bin-level storage, every product receives a unique physical address in the warehouse &mdash; a specific shelf, row, and bin number tracked in our WMS. This enables 30-second order picking, 99.7% accuracy, and instant inventory lookups. Bulk storage simply piles goods in a zone, leading to slow retrieval and frequent errors.</p></div></div>
