<!-- SEO ARTICLE -->
<section class="article-section">
<div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">GOOD TO KNOW</div>
<h2>Warehouse management systems for e-commerce: how WMS transforms storage operations</h2>
<div class="article-content">
<h3>Why a WMS is non-negotiable for modern warehousing</h3>
<p>A warehouse without a WMS is a room with shelves. A warehouse with a WMS is a precision logistics machine. The difference is measurable: manual order picking takes 5-10 minutes per order with an error rate of 3-8%. WMS-driven picking at MTP Group takes 30 seconds per order with a 99.7% accuracy rate. The system assigns every product a unique barcode, every bin a physical address, and every order an optimized picking route. This is not an incremental improvement &mdash; it is a fundamentally different approach to warehouse operations.</p>

<h3>Bin-level vs pallet-level storage: choosing the right model</h3>
<p>The storage model you need depends on your product characteristics. Bin-level addressed storage is designed for small and medium items &mdash; cosmetics, accessories, electronics, clothing &mdash; stored in individual bins on multi-tier shelving. Each bin has a unique address (e.g., A-12-03), enabling instant location lookup and rapid picking. Pallet-level storage is for heavy, bulky, or high-volume items stored on reinforced racking with forklift access. MTP Group offers both models across our two warehouses, and many clients use a hybrid approach: fast-moving SKUs in bins for quick picking, bulk reserve inventory on pallets.</p>

<h3>Inventory auditing: real-time accuracy vs annual counts</h3>
<p>Traditional warehouses conduct inventory counts once or twice a year &mdash; a disruptive multi-day process that halts operations. Modern WMS-equipped warehouses use rolling cycle counts: a portion of inventory is verified daily using barcode scanners, ensuring continuous accuracy without operational interruptions. At MTP Group, full reconciliation reports are available within 24 hours if any discrepancy is detected. Your dashboard displays live stock levels at all times, and automated alerts trigger when any SKU drops below your configured reorder threshold.</p>

<h3>Climate control and product-specific storage requirements</h3>
<p>Not all products can share the same environment. Cosmetics degrade at high temperatures. Electronics are damaged by humidity. Pharmaceuticals require strict temperature ranges. MTP Group maintains both warehouses at 15-25&deg;C with continuous humidity monitoring. The Bilohorodka warehouse includes FEFO (First Expired, First Out) zones for products with expiration dates &mdash; the WMS automatically prioritizes older stock for dispatch, preventing waste and compliance issues.</p>

<h3>Storage-only vs full fulfillment: what to choose</h3>
<p>Not every business needs full fulfillment services. Some clients use MTP Group's warehouse purely for storage &mdash; they maintain their own shipping operations but benefit from our climate-controlled, WMS-tracked, secure facility. Storage-only pricing starts from 650 UAH per cubic metre per month. Other clients start with storage and gradually transition to full fulfillment as their order volume grows. The transition is seamless because their inventory is already barcoded and tracked in our WMS.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

